"title": "8667: praise, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8667: praise, examples of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture provides many examples of individuals who praised God. These examples illustrate the variety of ways and methods in which God can be praised, as well as the motivation for that praise.</p>\n<h2>OT examples of those who praised God</h2>\n<h3>Melchizedek</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:18-Gen14:20\">GEN 14:18–14:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1-Exod15:2\">EXO 15:1–15:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jethro</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:9-Exod18:10\">EXO 18:9–18:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:10-1Chr29:13\">1CH 29:10–29:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Ezra</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:6\">NEH 8:6</a></strong></p>\n<h2>NT examples of those who praised God</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21\">LUK 10:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Zechariah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:67-Luke1:68\">LUK 1:67–1:68</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The shepherds</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:20\">LUK 2:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Simeon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:28\">LUK 2:28</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:37\">LUK 19:37</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46-Acts2:47\">ACT 2:46–2:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:50-Luke24:53\">LUK 24:50–24:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a></p>\n<h3>Those who were healed by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:35-Luke18:43\">LUK 18:35–18:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:1-Acts3:10\">ACT 3:1–3:10</a></p>\n<h3>The citizens of heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:2-Rev15:3\">REV 15:2–15:3</a></strong></p>",
